 Quick Redirects (this was a new feature in ...\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"dfischer\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1216:\"<p>Sorry for any issues with the latest plugin upgrade &#8211; in certain installs, the &#8216;use with jQuery&#8217; option is causing some issues with URLs and links in some or all browsers. To get around this until we have a fix in place, you can disable the &#8216;Use with jQuery&#8217; option. This will not keep the plugin from working, but just eliminates the features for the New Window and No Follow in the Quick Redirects (this was a new feature in 5.0).</p>\n<p>To turn off the &#8216;use with jQuery&#8217; feature:</p>\n<ul>\n<li> 1. Go to the plugin settings page &#8211; <strong>Redirect Options</strong>.</li>\n<li> 2. Uncheck the &#8216;Use with jQuery&#8217; feature.</li>\n<li> 3. Save the plugin settings.</li>\n<li> 4. &#8211; if you are using a caching plugin or WP_Cache, clear your cache files.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>That should eliminate the issue until we have a fix in place. If it does not, please <a href=\"mailto:plugins@fischercreativemedia.com\" target=\"_blank\">email us</a> a link to your site and what is happening and we will take a look as soon as we can  &#8211; please be sure to include the WP Version and the plugin name.</p>\n<p>Again, sorry for any issues this upgrade may have caused.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:113:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/help-my-site-is-not-working-correctly-after-upgrading-to-5-0-5-0-1/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"How can I get the plugin to work with XML-RPC posting?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/how-can-i-get-the-plugin-to-work-with-xml-rpc-posting/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:104:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/how-can-i-get-the-plugin-to-work-with-xml-rpc-posting/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 05 Nov 2012 04:28:40 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/?post_type=faqs&p=358\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:461:\"The plugin does not natively support XML-RPC posting because it uses protected meta keys for all of the redirects on pages/posts/custom post types. You can, however, easily add support to your theme to make it use the Quick Page Post Redirect plugin in any XML-RPC posts. Please be VERY careful using the WordPress theme editor to make changes to your functions.php file, as ANY typo (from you or even from me), can cause your site to stop working and cause ...\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"dfischer\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3699:\"<p>The plugin does not natively support XML-RPC posting because it uses protected meta keys for all of the redirects on pages/posts/custom post types. You can, however, easily add support to your theme to make it use the Quick Page Post Redirect plugin in any XML-RPC posts. <span style=\"color: #800000;\">Please be VERY careful using the WordPress theme editor to make changes to your functions.php file, as ANY typo (from you or even from me), can cause your site to stop working and cause you to have to use an FTP client to make any further changes to fix it.</span></p>\n<p>You need to be able to edit your <code>functions.php</code> file, and add the following code:</p>\n<div class=\"code-block\">\n<code>&lt;?php <span style=\"color: #000080;\">//&lt;- you may not need to add the php code opener or closer!</span><br />\nadd_action(\'init\', \'ppr_register_meta\');<br />\nfunction ppr_register_meta(){<br />\n<span style=\"color: #333399;\"> //do this for each meta field you want to use for each post_type</span><br />\n    register_meta( \'post\', \'<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">_pprredirect_active</span>\', \'ppr_sanitize_callback\', \'ppr_auth_callback\');<br />\n    register_meta( \'post\', \'<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">_pprredirect_newwindow</span>\', \'ppr_sanitize_callback\', \'ppr_auth_callback\');<br />\n    register_meta( \'post\', \'<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">_pprredirect_relnofollow</span>\', \'ppr_sanitize_callback\', \'ppr_auth_callback\');<br />\n    register_meta( \'post\', \'<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">_pprredirect_type</span>\', \'ppr_sanitize_callback\', \'ppr_auth_callback\');<br />\n    register_meta( \'post\', \'<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">_pprredirect_rewritelink</span>\', \'ppr_sanitize_callback\', \'ppr_auth_callback\');<br />\n    register_meta( \'post\', \'<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">_pprredirect_url</span>\', \'ppr_sanitize_callback\', \'ppr_auth_callback\');<br />\n    <span style=\"color: #333399;\">/***********</span><br />\n    <span style=\"color: #333399;\">    or use something like this to register for built-in and publicly_queryable types<br />\n    note that you need to uncomment this code to use it<br />\n    **</span><br />\n    $post_types=get_post_types(array(\'_builtin\' =&gt; true,\'publicly_queryable\' =&gt; true),\'names\',\'and\');<br />\n    foreach ($post_types as $post_type ) {<br />\n        register_meta( $post_type, \'_pprredirect_active\', \'ppr_sanitize_callback\', \'ppr_auth_callback\');<br />\n        register_meta( $post_type, \'_pprredirect_newwindow\', \'ppr_sanitize_callback\', \'ppr_auth_callback\');<br />\n        register_meta( $post_type, \'_pprredirect_relnofollow\', \'ppr_sanitize_callback\', \'ppr_auth_callback\');<br />\n        register_meta( $post_type, \'_pprredirect_type\', \'ppr_sanitize_callback\', \'ppr_auth_callback\');<br />\n        register_meta( $post_type, \'_pprredirect_rewritelink\', \'ppr_sanitize_callback\', \'ppr_auth_callback\');<br />\n        register_meta( $post_type, \'_pprredirect_url\', \'ppr_sanitize_callback\', \'ppr_auth_callback\');<br />\n    }<br />\n    <span style=\"color: #333399;\">***************/</span><br />\n}<br />\nfunction ppr_sanitize_callback($meta_value, $meta_key, $meta_type){<br />\n    <span style=\"color: #333399;\">//you can sanitize value here if needed.</span><br />\n    return $meta_value;<br />\n}<br />\nfunction ppr_auth_callback($can, $key, $post_id, $user_id, $cap, $caps){<br />\n    <span style=\"color: #333399;\">//you can set limitations in here to limit who you want to be able to use like :</span><br />\n    <span style=\"color: #333399;\">  /*</span><br />\n    if(user_can( $user_id, \'manage_options\' ))<br />\n        return true;<br />\n        <span style=\"color: #333399;\">*/</span><br />\n    return true;<br />\n}<br />\n?&gt;</code></div>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:100:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/how-can-i-get-the-plugin-to-work-with-xml-rpc-posting/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"How Many Quick Redirects can I add?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/how-many-quick-redirects-can-i-add/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/how-many-quick-redirects-can-i-add/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 05 Nov 2012 05:19:19 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/?post_type=faqs&p=354\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:438:\"As many as you want. There is not any limit set by the plugin, however, if you are having problems getting them to save, you may need to increase your WordPress memory settings or your php post limits or execution time. If there are a lot of items to save, the default settings may not be enough to process all of them. Check WordPress support for information on how to increase these items for your type of install.<br />\nTo increase ...\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"dfischer\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1102:\"<p>As many as you want. There is not any limit set by the plugin, however, if you are having problems getting them to save, you may need to increase your WordPress memory settings or your php post limits or execution time. If there are a lot of items to save, the default settings may not be enough to process all of them. Check WordPress support for information on how to increase these items for your type of install.</p>\n<p>To increase your WordPress Memory, you can either add the following to the <code>wp-config.php</code> file:</p>\n<p><code>define(\'WP_MEMORY_LIMIT\', \'96M\'); // can be 32M, 64M, 96M, 128M, etc.</code></p>\n<p>Or you can add the following to your <code>functions.php</code> file after the opening<code> <&#63;php </code> tag:</p>\n<p><code>ini_set(\'memory_limit\', \'96M\'); // can be 32M, 64M, 96M, 128M, etc.</code></p>\n<p>Either way should work as long as your host allows increasing memory via php. It is also important to note that WordPress requires a minimum of 32MB to run, so the more plugins and functionality you have in website, the more memory you may need have set.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:81:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/how-many-quick-redirects-can-i-add/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"I Can’t Select The ‘Use With jQuery’ Option, Why Not?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/i-cant-select-the-use-with-jquery-option-why-not/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:99:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/i-cant-select-the-use-with-jquery-option-why-not/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 20 Feb 2013 20:18:20 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/?post_type=faqs&p=407\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:354:\"That is because we decided to disable it for the time being.<br />\nThe last update was causing all sorts of jQuery conflicts, so we turned it off until we have had the time to work out the bugs. It will come back in a future update. Until then, you cannot use the &#8216;new window&#8217; or &#8216;no follow&#8217; features for Quick redirects.<br />\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"dfischer\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:356:\"<p>That is because we decided to disable it for the time being.</p>\n<p>The last update was causing all sorts of jQuery conflicts, so we turned it off until we have had the time to work out the bugs. It will come back in a future update. Until then, you cannot use the &#8216;new window&#8217; or &#8216;no follow&#8217; features for Quick redirects.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/i-cant-select-the-use-with-jquery-option-why-not/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"I Have a lot of Redirects to Add, Can I Bulk Import Them?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/i-have-a-lot-of-redirects-can-i-bulk-import-them/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:99:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/i-have-a-lot-of-redirects-can-i-bulk-import-them/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 06 Nov 2012 20:05:23 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/?post_type=faqs&p=366\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:451:\"Yes, you can.<br />\nWith the latest version (5.0+), you can bulk import redirects. Although, I always recommend that if you have over a few dozen redirects, that you look into setting up some .htaccess rules if at all possible, as the draw on the server is a lot less, you can add large numbers of redirects if needed.<br />\nYou need to set your redirects up in a text (.txt) file, one per line, PIPE separated with the redirect first, destination ...\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"dfischer\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1498:\"<p>Yes, you can.</p>\n<p>With the latest version (5.0+), you can bulk import redirects. Although, I always recommend that if you have over a few dozen redirects, that you look into setting up some .htaccess rules if at all possible, as the draw on the server is a lot less, you can add large numbers of redirects if needed.</p>\n<p>You need to set your redirects up in a text (.txt) file, one per line, PIPE separated with the redirect first, destination URL second, new window flag third, and no follow flag last, as in the below example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-block\"><code>redirect|destination|0|1<br />\n/old-link.htm|http://example.com/|1|0<br />\n/test/|http://testing.com/something/|1|1<br />\n... and so on</code></div>\n<p>To add bulk redirects, go to the plugin settings/options page (Redirect Options) and the fist section there is import/export capability. If you have backed up or exported your Quick Redirects, you can choose to import and replace the existing ones. If you just want to add, or add to existing Quick Redirects, click the &#8216;ADD TO Redirects&#8217; button . Then select the text file with your redirects and click the &#8220;ADD TO Current Redirects&#8221; button to begin the import.</p>\n<p><strong>Please Note</strong> that the file contents for exported redirects and the format for the contents of the file for adding redirects is VERY different for the ENCODED export. Use the PIPE separated export if you want to be able to edit the contents of the export file.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/i-have-a-lot-of-redirects-can-i-bulk-import-them/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"I read there are action hooks and filters… how do I use them?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/i-read-there-are-action-hooks-and-filters-how-do-i-use-them/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:110:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/i-read-there-are-action-hooks-and-filters-how-do-i-use-them/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 23 Feb 2013 20:30:54 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/?post_type=faqs&p=410\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:425:\"There are a few action hooks and filters in plugin. To use them, you need to be familiar with what a hook or filter is &#8211; so if you don&#8217;t know, stop reading now as this will probably not help you. If you do know and want to use the functionality, then read on.<br />\nThere are 3 action hooks and 1 filter in the plugin. They allow you to override the default functionality of the plugin in different ways. They ...\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"dfischer\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4704:\"<p>There are a few action hooks and filters in plugin. To use them, you need to be familiar with what a hook or filter is &#8211; so if you don&#8217;t know, stop reading now as this will probably not help you. If you do know and want to use the functionality, then read on.</p>\n<p>There are 3 action hooks and 1 filter in the plugin. They allow you to override the default functionality of the plugin in different ways. They are:</p>\n<h3>Quick Redirects</h3>\n<p>This hooks allows you to override the action if a Quick Redirect JUST before it does the actual redirecting. This is helpful if you want to check for some variable first and then decide if you should still redirect. There are other possible uses, but here is an example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-block\"><code>add_action(\'qppr_redirect\',\'some_callback_function\',10,2);<br />\nfunction some_callback_function($redirectURL, $redirect_type){<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if(current_user_can(\'update_core\')){<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;break;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;return;<br />\n}</code></div>\n<p>In this example, if the user is logged in and has update core permissions (i.e., an admin) then the redirect does NOT happen.</p>\n<h3>Regular Redirects</h3>\n<p>This hook allows for overriding the action of a regular Redirect (one set up on a page or post or custom post type) JUST before it redirects. You can use this to check for a variable or instance before deciding to let the redirect happen. It works just like the Quick Redirect hook, but is for regular redirects instead of quick redirects. An example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-block\"><code>add_action(\'qppr_do_redirect\',\'some_callback_function2\',10,2);<br />\nfunction some_callback_function2($redirectURL, $redirect_type){<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (strpos(\'google\',$_SERVER[\'HTTP_REFERER\'])!== false) {<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;$redirectURL = \'http://somenewlocation.com/google-referred/\';<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;wp_redirect($redirectURL,$redirect_type);<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;die();<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;return;<br />\n}</code></div>\n<p>This example checks to see if the person came directly from a Google page before coming to your redirect page. If so, it sends them someplace else, if not, they go to whatever redirect you initially set up.</p>\n<h3>Meta Redirects</h3>\n<p>This one has an action hook and a filter. It allows for overriding the action of a regular Redirect that has a redirect type specifically set to &#8216;meta&#8217;. You can use one or the other &#8211; depends on your preference - because the action hook gives you the arguments you can use them to check or modify the header call, where as the filter provides the fully formatted meta tag and message that you can then put back into the page via wp_head or the_content filters, etc.. Remember meta refreshes actually load page headers and content and the redirect happens after that is output to the browser and you can set a time frame before it redirects the user. Quick Redirects and Regular redirects happen before anything is output to the browser so they appear seamless.</p>\n<p>An example of the action hook is:</p>\n<div class=\"code-block\"><code>add_action(\'ppr_meta_head_hook\',\'some_callback_function3\',10,3);<br />\nfunction some_callback_function3($refresh_url=\'\',$refresh_secs=0,$messages=\'\'){<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;echo \'&lt;meta http-equiv=\"refresh\" content=\"\'.$refresh_secs.\'; URL=\'.$refresh_url.\'\" /&gt;\'.\"\\n\";<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;echo \'&lt;div id=\"ppr_custom_message\"&gt;\'. $messages.\'&lt;/div&gt;\'.\"\\n\";<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;return;<br />\n}</code></div>\n<p>An example of the filter is:</p>\n<div class=\"code-block\"><code>add_filter(\'ppr_meta_head_hook_filter\',\'override_ppr_metahead_new\',10,2);<br />\nfunction override_ppr_metahead_new($meta_tag=\'\',$meta_message=\'\'){<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;$meta = $meta_tag;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;$functiona = create_function(\'$content\', \'return \\\'&lt;div id=\"ppr_custom_message\"&gt;sample message override&lt;/div&gt;\\\';\');<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;$functionb = create_function(\'$title\', \'return \\\'sample message override TITLE\\\';\');<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;add_filter(\'get_content\',$functiona,100,1);<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;add_filter(\'get_title\',$functionb,100,1);<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;return $meta;<br />\n}</code></div>\n<p>Note how the filter completely changes the message and title of the page but leave the meta tag alone, and the action hook creates new meta tag and message.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:106:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/i-read-there-are-action-hooks-and-filters-how-do-i-use-them/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"What is New in version 5.0.3 – do I need to update?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/what-is-new-in-version-5-0-3-do-i-need-to-update/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:99:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/what-is-new-in-version-5-0-3-do-i-need-to-update/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 23 Feb 2013 19:42:56 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}